🫶 Favorite RP Moment
I loved playing Goat Joy, a naive alien who started hanging out with a human, Cat, who introduced her to all kinds of new experiences—especially food. Here’s a little snippet from our RP that captures one of my favorite moments:

Goat Joy reaches into the bag and pulls out beef jerky. With a sour face, she says,
“Not... ideal.”

She reaches in again, digging deep into the bag until her arm is past the elbow. This time, she pulls out a bouquet of carrots.

“Yummy, but I was hoping for something salty,” she smirks.

She opens the bag and tries to peer into it but can’t see through the darkness.

Goat Joy blindly reaches into the bag one more time—and pulls out a batch of fries, fresh out of the fryer.
“Perfect.”

She stuffs a small handful into her mouth before offering some to Cat, her mouth still partially full.

“Did you want some fries or something else from the bag?” she asks.

Cat nods eagerly but still reaches into the bag himself, fishing for something. After a couple of fancy moves, he pulls out a bouquet of red flowers and hands them to Goat.

He figures she’ll probably just eat them, but they’re hers to enjoy however she likes.

Goat Joy smiles and blushes at the gift. Luckily, her cravings are strong for the fries, so the flowers won’t be eaten... for now.

She stuffs another small handful of fries into her mouth. Then she takes Cat’s free hand and rests it next to hers, gently stroking the back of it.
